===Etymology===
From Ancient Greek [[ἐκπύρωσις]] (ecpyrōsis) "conflagration, [[ecpyrosis]]", referring in [[w:Stoic philosophy|Stoic philosophy]] to the destruction and recreation of the world in fire.  Coined by Paul Steinhardt.

